      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TIGGERLONG SASSY (1) turned in a better effort at Wagga last start, finishing third behind Ray Of Eve (18.30) in a Grade 4/5. Has performed well from this box with a win and nine minor placings to her name from 19 starts. Can find winning form. VINTAGE MEL (4) jumped well and was a winner (18.35) two back from a tricky draw then last start drew a squeeze box again but got further back and finished 5th at Richmond (18.91). Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Deserves plenty of respect. LUCKY WINNER (8) goes very well this course and distance starting 23 times for eight wins and six minors. Placed last time (19.93) at this track in a Mix 2/3, finishing third and beaten 1.3 lengths. Looks one of the chances. SUTTON BOLT (2) should be thereabouts despite an unplaced run here most recently.",
